{"article_id":"hWH2rVPRyM46U6HA","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"In the novel coronavirus , President Donald Trump has finally met a problem","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that can ' t be solved with his usual bag of political tools :","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"obfuscation , denial , deflecting blame , and misinformation .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"That hasn ' t stopped him from trying ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"even if it means saying things","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"that endanger public health .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"As of March 12 , the US has seen 1,323 confirmed cases of Covid-19 , the disease","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"stemming from the coronavirus ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"and 38 deaths ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"according to the Johns Hopkins tracker .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"Public health officials ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"including those in his own administration ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"now estimate","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that millions of people may eventually be infected with Covid-19 .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"\" If we are complacent","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"and don ' t do really aggressive containment and mitigation ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"the number could go way up","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"and be involved in many , many millions. \"","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Dr. Anthony Fauci , director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases and a member of the White House coronavirus task force , told the House Oversight Committee yesterday .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Trump ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"who addressed the nation from the Oval Office Wednesday night ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"has consistently sought to downplay the public health risk of the burgeoning pandemic","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"while his administration has been slow to respond to the crisis .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"Perhaps most concerning has been Trump ' s instinct","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"to outright contradict the facts and statements of the government ' s top infectious disease experts","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"as his administration has struggled to contain the outbreak .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"Here are seven of his coronavirus lies .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"Trump ' s statement to the nation Wednesday evening was his most serious treatment of the outbreak to date .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"He \" injected gravity and even a sense of crisis into a topic","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"that he and right-wing media have downplayed for weeks ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"\" making it a \" critical step in the right direction , \"","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"' s Kelsey Piper explained .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"Unfortunately , it was also deeply flawed .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Several of his statements , like a trade restriction with Europe along with his travel ban , had to be swiftly walked back by White House officials .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"Trump was unclear about exempting American citizens and permanent residents from the ban ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"leading to panicked crowds","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"congregating in enclosed spaces at many European airports like Charles de Gaulle in Paris , France .","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"Bedlam at U.S.-bound airlines at CDG in Paris early this a.m. ,","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"as Americans pay as much as $ 20,000 for last-minute flights .","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"pic.twitter.com/kkbOAEFn4Y","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"- Mike McIntire","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"( @ mmcintire )","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"March 12 , 2020","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Perhaps most egregious was his claim","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"that major insurance companies would cover treatment for Covid-19 free of charge ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"when in actuality they had agreed only to coronavirus testing","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"without a co-pay .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Trump 's claim tonight","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"that health insurers `` have agreed to waive all copayments for coronavirus treatments ''","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"seems to be news to them .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"\" For testing .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"Not for treatment. \"","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"a spokesperson for the major insurance lobby AHIP says .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"- Sarah Owermohle","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"( @ owermohle )","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"March 12 , 2020","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"While Trump ' s speech Wednesday evening finally sent a signal to the American public","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"that the novel coronavirus is very serious ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"the mixed-up details undermined the endeavor .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"In a phone interview with Sean Hannity on March 4 , Trump contradicted public health experts ' estimates of the death rate for Covid-19","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"- based on a \" hunch . \"","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"To be sure ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"a precise death rate for Covid-19 is difficult to measure ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"in part because testing hasn ' t been done on a large enough scale","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"to measure accurately .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"Earlier this month , the World Health Organization had the death rate pegged at about 3.4 percent .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"Many experts think","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"that number may be too high ,","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"given the struggles with adequate testing ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"putting the true number likely closer to 1 percent .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Trump , however , told Fox viewers","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"that the death rate was even lower","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"- a \" fraction of 1 percent \" -","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"based on his \" hunch. \"","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"Here ' s the rest of the quote :","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"Now , this is just my hunch ,","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"but based on a lot of conversations with a lot of people","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"that do this ,","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"because a lot of people will have this","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"and it is very mild ...","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"So if ,","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"you know ,","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"we have thousands or hundreds of thousands of people","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"that get better ,","depth":16},{"id":84,"text":"just by ,","depth":17},{"id":85,"text":"you know ,","depth":19},{"id":86,"text":"sitting around","depth":19},{"id":87,"text":"and even going to work ,","depth":18},{"id":88,"text":"some of them go to work ,","depth":15},{"id":89,"text":"but they get better","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"and then ,","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"when you do have a death","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"like you had in the state of Washington ,","depth":16},{"id":93,"text":"like you had one in California ,","depth":17},{"id":94,"text":"I believe","depth":18},{"id":95,"text":"you had one in New York ,","depth":18},{"id":96,"text":"you know ,","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"all of a sudden it seems like 3 or 4 percent ,","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"which is a very high number ,","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"as opposed to a fraction of 1 percent .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"Trump may have sought to downplay the mortality risk of Covid-19","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"in order to reassure nervous Americans and a jittery economy ,","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"but instead created a much more dangerous situation","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"where people weren ' t taking the virus seriously enough .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"It ' s true that the risk of dying is highest for elderly people and immunocompromised people","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"( the US has plenty of both ) ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"but","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"as ' s Dylan Scott and Eliza Barclay explained ,","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"\" the speed","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"at which the outbreak plays out","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"matters hugely for its consequences \" :","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"What epidemiologists fear most is the health care system becoming overwhelmed by a sudden explosion of illness","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"that requires more people to be hospitalized","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"than it can handle .","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"In that scenario , more people will die","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"because there won ' t be enough hospital beds or ventilators","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"to keep them alive .","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"So not taking the virus seriously","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"- at the bureaucratic and individual levels -","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"means fewer people","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"taking suitable precautions , and possibly more cases and more deaths .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"3 ) \" It ' s going to disappear .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"One day ,","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"it ' s like a miracle ,","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"it will disappear \"","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"On February 28 , Trump said","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"that coronavirus will \" disappear \" like a \" miracle \"","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"while speaking at a press conference for his coronavirus task force .","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"On Tuesday , he told reporters on Capitol Hill","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"that coronavirus \" will go away. \"","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"In late February , he speculated","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"that warm weather would kill the virus","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"and stop its spread .","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"None of these statements are backed by science or infectious disease experts within his own administration .","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"( Though some diseases","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"- like the seasonal flu - do diminish in warmer seasons ,","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"there is currently no evidence","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"the novel coronavirus will behave this way . )","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"Experts all along have predicted","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"without drastic measures","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"to prevent outbreaks from growing bigger or the rapid development of a vaccine ,","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"the novel coronavirus will likely continue spreading","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"and become endemic , a regular disease like the common cold .","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"On March 7","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"while visiting the CDC in Atlanta , Georgia ,","depth":7},{"id":146,"text":"Trump said","depth":6},{"id":147,"text":"that anyone","depth":7},{"id":148,"text":"who wants a test for Covid-19","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"can get one .","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"As countless viral Twitter threads , local news stories , and more have recounted ,","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"that promise has not rung true .","depth":6},{"id":152,"text":"Take the \" Kafkaesque \" story","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"physician ' s assistant Julie Eaker told ' s Brian Resnick and Dylan Scott","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"about trying to get one patient tested in California :","depth":7},{"id":155,"text":"First , Eaker called her local health department","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"and was told","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"her patient didn ' t qualify for testing","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"since they hadn ' t traveled to China ,","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"per the guidelines from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention at the time .","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"After the CDC relaxed its testing criteria ,","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"the patient was still sick ,","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"so Eaker called again .","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"\" I didn ' t receive a phone call back , \"","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"she says .","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"The patient thought","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"they had pneumonia","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"and asked to be tested for peace of mind .","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"Finally , last week ,","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"after Eaker ordered some test kits herself from a private lab ,","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"she got a call back .","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"\" The health department told me","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"I was not allowed to use those test kits","depth":15},{"id":173,"text":"-","depth":15},{"id":174,"text":"that I ordered -","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"without their permission ! \"","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"Eaker was horrified .","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"So she called the CDC","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"to confirm","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"if the local health department was correct .","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"\" I did not get through , \"","depth":11},{"id":181,"text":"she says .","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"\" I spent hours and hours and hours on hold . ...","depth":10},{"id":183,"text":"So I thought","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"I would just call the White House","depth":11},{"id":185,"text":"and talk to Vice President Pence ,","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"who is in charge of the coronavirus task force. \"","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"She didn ' t get Pence ,","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"but a White House switchboard operator told her to call the CDC .","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"\" Somebody has got to help us , \"","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"she says ,","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"exasperated .","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"\" We ' re out here on the front lines","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"trying to take care of people . \"","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"But the problem has been bigger than that .","depth":8},{"id":195,"text":"The administration had promised to quickly deliver 1 million testing kits to private labs .","depth":9},{"id":196,"text":"But on March 6 , the White House announced","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"that it would fall far short of that goal for testing kit distribution .","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"According to virologists ,","depth":10},{"id":199,"text":"the best way","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"to prevent an outbreak of a highly contagious virus like coronavirus","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"is through aggressive testing .","depth":11},{"id":202,"text":"Knowing who is infected and when they became infected","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"allows traditional measures like quarantines to work more effectively .","depth":13},{"id":204,"text":"If people don ' t know","depth":14},{"id":205,"text":"they have it ,","depth":14},{"id":206,"text":"they aren ' t able to take their own steps","depth":14},{"id":207,"text":"to prevent spreading it to others .","depth":14},{"id":208,"text":"In that , the administration has failed .","depth":11},{"id":209,"text":"So far , the US only has a limited capacity","depth":12},{"id":210,"text":"to process coronavirus tests every day ,","depth":12},{"id":211,"text":"meaning we likely don ' t have accurate numbers for the scale of this virus ' s spread .","depth":11},{"id":212,"text":"The CDC has recommended","depth":10},{"id":213,"text":"that hospitalized patients","depth":12},{"id":214,"text":"displaying Covid-19 symptoms ,","depth":12},{"id":215,"text":"as well as those","depth":13},{"id":216,"text":"who belong to at-risk populations ,","depth":13},{"id":217,"text":"should get priority for testing ,","depth":12},{"id":218,"text":"but anecdotal accounts of people with symptoms","depth":11},{"id":219,"text":"being denied a test","depth":11},{"id":220,"text":"have begun popping up on social medial .","depth":10},{"id":221,"text":"At first , Trump blamed an Obama-era FDA rule for its slow response","depth":8},{"id":222,"text":"in distributing test kits ,","depth":8},{"id":223,"text":"but experts have since revealed that claim to be false .","depth":7},{"id":224,"text":"During that March 4 call with Hannity , Trump also compared coronavirus with the flu .","depth":8},{"id":225,"text":"He mentioned","depth":11},{"id":226,"text":"that the flu kills anywhere between 27,000 and 77,000 people every year ,","depth":11},{"id":227,"text":"implying","depth":11},{"id":228,"text":"that coronavirus isn ' t as serious of a threat to public health as Influenza .","depth":11},{"id":229,"text":"3 . Suggests","depth":11},{"id":230,"text":"it 's fine for people w/ Covid-19 to go to work","depth":11},{"id":231,"text":"4 . Compares coronavirus to `` the regular flu , ''","depth":11},{"id":232,"text":"indicating","depth":12},{"id":233,"text":"he does n't get the difference","depth":12},{"id":234,"text":"pic.twitter.com/uC9c03zX31","depth":7},{"id":235,"text":"- Aaron Rupar","depth":8},{"id":236,"text":"( @ atrupar )","depth":8},{"id":237,"text":"March 5 , 2020","depth":7},{"id":238,"text":"Trump ' s own infectious disease experts have said","depth":6},{"id":239,"text":"that idea is wrong .","depth":6},{"id":240,"text":"Dr. Fauci told Congress on March 11","depth":7},{"id":241,"text":"that \" the mortality of [ Covid-19 ] is multiple times what the seasonal flu is . \"","depth":7},{"id":242,"text":"The reason why lies in the numbers .","depth":7},{"id":243,"text":"The CDC estimates","depth":9},{"id":244,"text":"that the seasonal flu has resulted in between 9.3 million and 49 million illnesses in the US each year since 2010 ,","depth":10},{"id":245,"text":"putting the flu ' s death rate at about 0.1 percent .","depth":10},{"id":246,"text":"Even if WHO ' s 3.4 percent death rate for coronavirus is high due to inadequate testing capacity ,","depth":10},{"id":247,"text":"using other public health expert ' s estimations of around 1 percent would mean","depth":11},{"id":248,"text":"that Covid-19 could be as much as 10 times deadlier than the seasonal flu .","depth":11},{"id":249,"text":"If 49 million Americans were to be infected with the coronavirus ,","depth":10},{"id":250,"text":"a 1 percent death rate would cause 490,000 deaths , much more than the flu .","depth":10},{"id":251,"text":"On February 25 , Trump promised","depth":5},{"id":252,"text":"that a vaccine would be available soon .","depth":5},{"id":253,"text":"\" Now they have it ,","depth":6},{"id":254,"text":"they have studied it ,","depth":7},{"id":255,"text":"they know very much ,","depth":7},{"id":256,"text":"in fact , we ' re very close to a vaccine , \"","depth":6},{"id":257,"text":"Trump said during a state visit to India .","depth":6},{"id":258,"text":"That simply isn ' t possible","depth":9},{"id":259,"text":"even if development of a vaccine were prioritized","depth":10},{"id":260,"text":"and pushed through the regulatory process as fast as possible","depth":10},{"id":261,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":262,"text":"as pharmaceutical executives explained to Trump himself .","depth":7},{"id":263,"text":"Dr. Fauci estimates","depth":7},{"id":264,"text":"that it would be at least a year or a year and a half","depth":8},{"id":265,"text":"before a vaccine would be available to the general public .","depth":8},{"id":266,"text":"Several potential vaccine solutions for coronavirus are in early development in China ,","depth":6},{"id":267,"text":"but Daniel O ' Day , CEO of Gilead Sciences , told Trump","depth":7},{"id":268,"text":"that those are only now entering clinical trials .","depth":7},{"id":269,"text":"It ' s likely that a vaccine will eventually be developed and available to the general public ,","depth":5},{"id":270,"text":"but it ' s not going to save us from this current outbreak .","depth":5},{"id":271,"text":"7 ) The US was \" most prepared country in the world \"","depth":3},{"id":272,"text":"Trump has repeatedly claimed","depth":6},{"id":273,"text":"that the US was the most prepared country in the world .","depth":6},{"id":274,"text":"This is , frankly , Trump ' s usual political bluster .","depth":5},{"id":275,"text":"The reality is that his administration , with the help of a Republican-controlled Congress , hampered the country ' s ability","depth":8},{"id":276,"text":"to fight pandemics like Covid-19 ,","depth":8},{"id":277,"text":"as explained by ' s Matthew Yglesias :","depth":7},{"id":278,"text":"In fact , the Trump administration remains committed to cutting funding","depth":7},{"id":279,"text":"to fight potential pandemics .","depth":7},{"id":280,"text":"When confronted in a congressional hearing about a 15 percent cut of $ 1.2 billion to the CDC and a $ 35 million decrease to the Infectious Diseases Rapid Response Reserve Fund ' s annual contribution in the White House ' s proposed 2021 budget ,","depth":6},{"id":281,"text":"acting director of the White House Office of Management and Budget Russ Vought defended the proposed cuts .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":563,"left":532,"right":562,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":532,"left":425,"right":531,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":425,"left":300,"right":424,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":287,"right":299,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":287,"left":284,"right":286,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":284,"left":0,"right":283,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":286,"left":3,"right":285,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":290,"right":298,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":290,"left":289,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":289,"left":288,"right":8,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":288,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":293,"right":297,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":293,"left":292,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":292,"left":291,"right":12,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":291,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":296,"right":18,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":294,"right":295,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":294,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":295,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":424,"left":336,"right":423,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":336,"left":307,"right":335,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":307,"left":306,"right":26,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":303,"right":305,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":303,"left":301,"right":302,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":301,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":21,"right":22,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":305,"left":23,"right":304,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":304,"left":24,"right":25,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":335,"left":322,"right":334,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":322,"left":311,"right":321,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":311,"left":27,"right":310,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":310,"left":309,"right":31,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":309,"left":308,"right":30,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":308,"left":28,"right":29,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":321,"left":32,"right":320,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":320,"left":317,"right":319,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":317,"left":33,"right":316,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":